Recipe for Bolonegnese
1. Cut into small cubes - carrots, celery and white onion
2. Fry well until softened
3. Add half a kilo of meat
4. Stir until the meat is burnt
5. Add a touch of red wine and wait for it to evaporate
6. Add Mutti tomato sauce and water
7. Cook it until boil and lower the fire
8. Let it cook for about an hour and a half
9. Finally enjoy, Buono buono

